name: rock ring with pearl beads from washington territory
description:
This is a wrapped ring size 6.
The stone holds healing qualities and was
found in river bed near in Oregon. More Apache
than Rococo in feeling. The twisting copper wire
feels french!

name: Irredescent feathers and beads exposed on bosom
description:
15" necklace with pretty claps done in a pinky
and rose colorway in a Rococo style with rasberry
colored feathers. The center piece falls nicely to show off
your colar bones.

name: Looking glass beads entwine with french finery necklace plus eagle nest ring
description:
This set has glass beads mixed with pearl beads. The center has an intesting light 14k gold wire piece. The ring is made from 14Kgold
with one lonely pearl bead- a sweet egg if you will. The band is copper. The ring conforms to all sizes. The necklace is 15".

name: chandelier ring and beads laced together banded ring
description:
Here are two rings the larger one, the chandelier ring has a rococo designed band and is adjustable. price is 65.00

The smaller beaded laced together ring is 45.00.
There are both rococo influenced and match everything due to their vibrant colors!

name: Boucher enraptured with turquoise necklace with Turquoise french kiss ring
description: This 16" necklace has pearl and turquoise beads with a pretty claps in the back. Along with the necklace is a size 6 bright Turquoise ring.
